Instead of the jokes being that they hate each other, the jokes are more about that they like each other and Taz hates everything. Vince and Michael Cole had nothing in common. Vince sounded completely generic and unoffensive to the point if nobody told you or showed you it was Vince McMahon spealing, you'd have never realized it.

Bayley's Michael Cole hate schtick comes from the fact his voice is so imposingly distinct and grating that he doesn't just blend in to the action of the match like Vince does but instead is left competing for your attention with it and distracting you.

Not to say JR and Jerry Lawler weren't distinct, but Lawler made no pretense to professional commentary, and when JR wasn't doing his BAH GAWD level of emotion, he sounded pretty much exactly like Vince did except with a more noticeable southern drawl.

I repeat, Vince and JR sounded more or less alike, and JR has the more outstanding reputation for commentary because he hammed it up in ways Vince never did. Vince's announcer voice was specifically meant not to stand out.

>>8286397
ratio is your download vs upload. a ratio of 1 would equal you uploading 100% of the amount of data you downloaded. If you downloaded 10GB or 300GB you seeded back that same amount to have a 1 ratio. You generally want to have a ratio above a 1. This is achieved by seeding the torrent for many weeks and snagging some late comers.

xwt offers dozens and dozens of freeleech packs that will help you establish a positive ratio while you download the shit you really want. I recommend high traffic megapacks like WWF and WCW ppv collections, or full year packs of companies like NJPW. Remember, you don't have to download every file in those megapacks to generate an upload. For example, I only have 6GB of the entire 588GB torrent of WCW Saturday Night but have gotten over 650GB of upload in its 5 month lifespan.

Generally if you don't seed a 1:1 then having seeded a torrent for 3 days is enough to avoid getting the ire of the mods.

I recommend qbittorrent as a good torrent program, there's some quality of life improvements for the UI over others like utorrent.

xwt has gone invite only for the first time in its 15 years though to look like it's a credible tracker. (it's not, there's not even a bonus point system that's standard for everything) so you might wanna ask a friend or maybe they'll open up registrations for new years

>A young and ambitious Hayter came close to diving in at the deep end and relocating to America to chase her dream. But a quick search online changed her mind when she found a pair of wrestling schools 20 miles away. Her journey into the world of pro wrestling was about to begin.

>"At one point I was like, 'maybe I'll go to America and train at a school there for a few months' because I didn't even know if there was a pro wrestling school in the UK," she added. >Hayter grew into the pro-wrestling scene and performed at trainee shows in local community centres in front of a few dozen people. Her name grew around the British independent scene and she was soon getting calls from promoters who wanted to book her on to their shows.

Then I came to AEW, it's grand with a big stage and it's on TV, and I do always think back to that moment - it's very humbling and I still can't believe this is real."

>"I still get the same nerves and the same feelings as I did seven years ago when I first started, but it's on such a bigger scale.
